title.narrative: IMPROVED HEALTH & NUTRITION SERVICES

description.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and their families have increased access to nutrition and health services in targeted municipalities., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid), Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women (Covid), Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 children, adolescents, youth and their families, especially the most disadvantaged, are increasingly using improved quality basic services.

title.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and their families have increased access to nutrition and health services in targetedmunicipalities.

description.narrative: Through UNICEF support, targeted primary health care facilities provided basic service delivery in a safe and protective environment, in line with COVID-19 prevention and protective measures. Nutrition interventions focused on promoting optimal Infant and Young Child Feeding (IYCF) in particular. UNICEF advocated and provided technical support for ;the establishment of a nutrition unit at MOH’s Primary Healthcare Institute and initiation of health facility-based nutrition interventions, including screening (using MUAC), counseling and development and dissemination of IYCF material nationwide. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
